column5: Atlerless deer tag for bow season - WMU 85.  Prime Huron County deer grounds.  Got permission for a few thousand acres out that way.  Question for the other hunters.  Does entering a second choice for WMU reduce your chance of you getting your first choice?  I wanted 76, but didn't get it.  If I wouldn't have entered 85 as a second choice, would I still not have gotten 76 this year?  Also just applied for the Controlled Deer hunt over the phone.  Just a reminder, you have till Aug 31st.
I have about 14 or so doe tags here in Indiana on my lifetime license. It's crazy how many you can take here. Some places have really seen a decline. Most deer I have taken in 1 season is 5.
Nick I always put 76 in both boxes.Never missed yet,well except this year as I am going buck only anyways.Didnt apply.
Never thought about putting the same WMU for second choice too.  Clever.

I got mine as well.  Two years in a row for me.  Only been hunting for 3.  Call it good odds?  Being I hunt with my Ex's family, I consider it a security blanket for being able to join the club.....I have entered the same WMU in the second choice box.  Phone last year, office this year.
Got mine today too, insurance so i can get one for my friend who lets me hunt on his land.
Yeah, the huntin season's sneakin up on us..  Just dropped $120 at crappy tire on skeets and target load!  Gunna warm up the shoulder this weekend
Yup got mine today gonna practice on the Great Canadian Turd Despencers though, much more satisfying.   now to wait out the controlled  Peter
